## Release Notes

### Version 1.0.0 (Initial Release)

**Features:**
- Complete Databricks Asset Bundle structure
- Medallion Architecture (Bronze → Silver → Gold → Semantic)
- Multi-source ingestion (PostgreSQL, Salesforce, Azure Blob Storage)
- DLT transformation pipelines with data quality expectations
- Production-ready configuration with dev/test/prod deployment targets
- Comprehensive documentation
  - Architecture documentation
  - Deployment guide
  - Troubleshooting guide
  - Dashboard recreation guide

**Components:**
- databricks.yml - Main bundle configuration
- src/pipelines/ - DLT Python transformations (4 files)
- src/notebooks/ - Bronze/Gold/Semantic layer notebooks
- resources/ - Job and pipeline configuration definitions
- docs/ - Complete technical documentation (4 guides)
- requirements.txt - Python dependencies
- .gitignore - Git ignore patterns
- LICENSE - MIT License

**Pipelines:**
1. PostgreSQL Ingestion → retail_project.postgress_bronze
2. Salesforce Ingestion → retail_project.salesforce (SCD Type 2)
3. Blob Storage Ingestion → retail_project.blob_storge
4. DLT Transformation → Bronze → Silver → Gold layers

**Deployment:**
```bash
databricks bundle validate -t dev
databricks bundle deploy -t dev
databricks bundle run retail_job -t dev
```

**Known Issues:**
- Salesforce OAuth connection requires re-authentication (see Troubleshooting guide)
- Lakeview Dashboards must be recreated manually (see Dashboard_Recreation.md)

